The '''Church of Fatima''', a Roman Catholic church, is located in [[Bangui]], in the [[Central African Republic]]. 

It is situated in the neighborhood known as KM5 which is 5&nbsp;km away from the center of the city.<ref name="Woodfork2006">{{cite book|author=Jacqueline Cassandra Woodfork|title=Culture And Customs of the Central African Republic|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7SEWjJ0_w2oC&pg=PA145|accessdate=24 July 2013|date=1 January 2006|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|isbn=978-0-313-33203-6|pages=145–}}</ref>

On May 28, 2014, the Seleka, a paramilitary rebel movement, threw grenades before shooting indiscriminately at the church, killing at least 11 people.<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-27614401 CAR Seleka rebels kill many in Bangui church attack]. ''BBC''. Retrieved 2014-05-30.</ref>

