{{ref improve|date=February 2013}}
'''Cidona''' is an [[apple]]-based [[soft drink]] that has been on sale since 1955.  It is popular in [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]] and has some sales in the [[United Kingdom]].
[[File:Cidona.jpg|thumb|Cidona]]
It was once produced by cider producers [[Bulmers (Republic of Ireland)|Bulmers]] (part of [[Cantrell and Cochrane|C&C]])  and comes in a distinctive green bottle. It is now part of [[Britvic]] Ireland due to C&C selling their soft drink segment in 2007.<ref>[https://www.cnbc.com/id/18650788 Britvic Agrees to Buy C&C's Soft-Drinks Division] CNBC, 14 May 2007</ref>.

