[[Image:Канашский Суд.jpg|thumb|[[Kanashsky District]] Court in [[Chuvashia]].]]
The '''district courts of Russia''' ({{lang-ru|районный суд}} or {{lang|ru|городской суд}}; also called ''{{transl|ru|rayon}}'' or ''{{transl|ru|[[raion]]}}'' courts) are primarily courts of first instance in the [[judiciary of Russia]] but sometimes hear appeals from [[Magistrates' court (Russia)|magistrates' courts]].{{sfn|Terrill|2009|p=425}} They are formed in ''{{transl|ru|[[raion]]}}'' or areas ({{lang|ru|районах}}), urban areas ({{lang|ru|районах в городах}}), and cities ({{lang|ru|городах}}). Decisions of the court are appealed to the regional court.

As courts of first instance, they handle criminal cases where imprisonment is for more than 3 years, and consist of 1 [[judge]] and a [[jury]] where required.{{sfn|Terrill|2009|p=425}}{{sfn|Terrill|2009|p=439}} As courts of appeal from decisions of the [[magistrate courts of Russia|magistrate courts]] consisting of 1 [[justice of the peace (Russia)|justice of the peace]], they consist of 1 judge and retry the case.{{sfn|Terrill|2009|p=425}}

They were called People's Courts until 1996.{{sfn|Terrill|2009|p=425}}

