{{italic title}}
[[File:Alpenquai - ZSG 'Etzel' - Utoquai 2012-03-23 15-51-11 (P7000).JPG|thumb|right|The MS ''Etzel'']]
[[File:MS 'Etzel' - Alpenquai 2012-08-08 19-38-27 (WB850F).JPG|thumb|right|Under way]]
The '''MS ''Etzel''''' is a preserved [[motor ship]] on [[Lake Zürich]] in [[Switzerland]]. She was built for the [[Zürichsee-Schifffahrtsgesellschaft]] (Lake Zurich Navigation Company) in 1934, and operated for them until she was retired in 2001. She is now owned and operated by the Etzel society, a society specifically created to preserve her.<ref name=etzsta>{{cite web | url = http://www.msetzel.ch/136/Startseite.html | title = MS Etzel | language = German | publisher = MS Etzel | accessdate = 2012-03-24}}</ref>

The ''Etzel'' is named after the [[Etzel (mountain)|Etzel]], a mountain overlooking Lake Zurich. She was built by [[Escher Wyss & Cie.]], has an overall length of {{convert|31.9|m}}, an overall width of {{convert|5.7|m}}, and a capacity of 150 passengers.<ref name=etztec>{{cite web | url = http://www.msetzel.ch/207/Das_Schiff/Technische_Daten.html | title = MS Etzel - Technical Data | language = German | publisher = MS Etzel | accessdate = 2012-04-20}}</ref>

The ''Etzel'' is available for charter. In addition, the owning society organises occasional excursions aboard the vessel.<ref>{{cite web | title = MS Etzel - motor boat | url = http://www.zuerichsee.ch/en/page.cfm/experiencesrz/Excursions/1061 | publisher = Zürichsee Tourism | accessdate = 2012-04-23}}</ref>

