{{Infobox UNESCO World Heritage Site | image = Tigris River At Diyarbakir.JPG | image_upright = 1.2 | caption = | location = [[Diyarbakır]], [[Diyarbakır Province]], [[Şanlıurfa Subregion]], [[Southeast Anatolia Region (statistical)|Southeast Anatolia Region]], [[Turkey]] | part_of = [[Diyarbakır Fortress]] and Hevsel Gardens Cultural Landscape | criteria = {{UNESCO WHS type|(iv)}}(iv) | ID = 1488 | coordinates = {{coord|37|54|39.1|N|40|13|38.2|E|display=title, inline|format=dms}} | year = 2015 | locmapin = Turkey | map_caption = }} '''Hevsel Gardens''' ({{lang-tr|Hevsel Bahçeleri}}), are the seven hundred hectares fertile lands near [[Tigris]] shore, between the [[Diyarbakır Fortress]] and the river. The gardens were added to the [[UNESCO]] tentative list in 2013.<ref>[http://www.sabah.com.tr/turizm/2013/10/25/hevsel-bahceleri-de-unescoya-aday "Hevsel Bahçeleri de UNESCO'ya aday"].&#x20;</ref> It became a [[List of World Heritage Sites in Turkey|World Heritage Site]] in 2015, along with Diyarbakır Fortress.<ref>[http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/1488 "Diyarbakır Fortress and Hevsel Gardens Cultural Landscape"].&#x20;</ref> == References == {{Reflist}}
