{{Infobox mountain | name = Hogleifa | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 3278 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 151 | parent_peak = [[Wilerhorn (Bernese Alps)|Wilerhorn]] | prominence_ref = <ref>Retrieved from the [[Swisstopo]] topographic maps. The key col is the Chastlerjoch (3,127 m).</ref> | map = Switzerland | map_caption = Location in Switzerland | location = [[Valais]], [[Switzerland]] | range = [[Bernese Alps]] | coordinates = {{coord|46|22|15|N|7|47|35.2|E|type:mountain_region:CH_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
The '''Hogleifa''' is a [[mountain]] in the [[Bernese Alps]], overlooking the [[Lötschental]] in the canton of [[Valais]]. It lies at the western end of the [[Bietschhorn]]-[[Aletschhorn]] chain.
