{{Notability|date=February 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=May 2017}}
{{Infobox radio station | name = 94.3 Radio One | image = Radio-One-94.3-Logo.jpg | image_size = 180px | city = [[Mumbai]], [[Delhi]], [[Bangalore]], [[Ahmedabad]], [[Chennai]], [[Kolkata]] and [[Pune]] | area = National | branding = Radio One 94.3 | slogan = | airdate = | frequency = | format = | power = | erp = | class = | callsign_meaning = | former_callsigns = | owner = | website = {{url|http://www.radioone.in/|''Official website''}} }}
'''94.3 Radio One''' is a [[commercial radio]] network in [[India]]. It was launched on 18 September 2007{{citation needed|reason='List of FM radio stations in Bangalore' says August 1, 2006|date=November 2017}} with [[radio station|stations]] in the seven cities [[Mumbai]], [[Delhi]], [[Bangalore]], [[Ahmedabad]], [[Chennai]], [[Kolkata]] and [[Pune]].
The [[Radio network#Broadcasting networks|network]] is the only one [[Commercial broadcasting|broadcasting]] in English (called "international format") in all of India's three biggest cities: Mumbai, Delhi and Bangalore.<ref>{{cite web|title=94.3 Radio One Launches India’s First International Radio Network Brand|url=http://www.exchange4media.com/radio/94.3-radio-one-launches-india’s-first-international-radio-network-brand_67348.html|website=Exchange4media|accessdate=16 October 2017}}</ref> The other stations Pune, Kolkata, Chennai and Ahmedabad in the network broadcast Hindi formats only targeting an upscale educated audience. All stations broadcast at [[VHF|94.3 MHz]] except the one in Ahmedabad which is at 95.0&nbsp;MHz.
94.3 Radio One was [[Ranking|ranked]] as India's most attractive radio [[brand]] 2017 (out of two radio brands listed), and at place 531 among all brands, in the annual publication ''[[India's Most Attractive Brands]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=94.3 Radio One India Is Most Attractive Radio Brand: TRA Report|url=http://www.exchange4media.com/media-radio/943-radio-one-india-is-most-attractive-radio-brand-tra-report_87127.html|website=Exchange4media|accessdate=16 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=India's Most Attractive Brands 2017 Ranking|url=http://www.trustadvisory.info/tra/categorymab17.php|website=TRA Research|accessdate=16 October 2017}}</ref>
The network is owned by Next Radio Ltd, a [[subsidiary]] of [[Next MediaWorks]]. The [[Chief executive officer|Managing Director and CEO]] of Next Radio is Vineet Singh Hukmani. He is also a shareholder director in the company.<ref>{{cite web|author=Next Radio Ltd|title=Key People|url=http://www.radioone.in/key-people|website=Radio One 94.3|accessdate=16 October 2017}}</ref>
94.3 Radio One Delhi, Mumbai and Bangalore also stream live on ONLINE at http://1cast.in ( only in India) AND the company has also launched India's first online audio business channel - Business ONE, in January 2018 (the business channel operates 9am-4pm mon-fri) http://www.asiaradiotoday.com/news/radio-one-india-launches-live-streaming-radio-and-new-business-channel<nowiki/>.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.exchange4media.com/mediaradio/943-radio-one-india-launches-www1castin-new-audio-business-channel_87825.html|title=94.3 Radio One India launches www.1cast.in & new audio business channel|work=Indian Advertising Media & Marketing News – exchange4media|access-date=2018-08-20|language=en-US}}</ref>
94.3 Radio One celebrated its 11th anniversary in September 2018 by launching a pioneering 'audience tracker' , the first by any media company in India, that tracks the consumption habits of its upscale audience across brands and categories http://www.asiaradiotoday.com/news/943-radio-one-celebrates-11th-year-new-audience-tracker
